ivardefs.name: age
ivardefs.desc: The age at which this reference range is applicable. This is a neonatal age (e.g. number of weeks at term) if the meaning says so.

ivardefs.name: appliesTo_
ivardefs.desc: Codes to indicate the target population this reference range applies to.

ivardefs.name: category
ivardefs.desc: The category of interval of values for continuous or ordinal observations conforming to this ObservationDefinition.

ivardefs.name: condition
ivardefs.desc: Text based condition for which the reference range is valid.

ivardefs.name: context
ivardefs.desc: Codes to indicate the health context the range applies to. For example, the normal or therapeutic range.

ivardefs.name: gender
ivardefs.desc: Sex of the population the range applies to.

ivardefs.name: gestationalAge
ivardefs.desc: The gestational age to which this reference range is applicable, in the context of pregnancy.

ivardefs.name: range
ivardefs.desc: The low and high values determining the interval. There may be only one of the two.

properties.desc: Multiple  ranges of results qualified by different contexts for ordinal or continuous observations conforming to this ObservationDefinition.
